Some points:

It's in your best interest not to pollute your own environment since
you live in that environment. People who don't grasp this are often
self-destructive in other ways since there own bodies are part of
the environment, as well. So you are basically asking me why you
shouldn't take a dump in the kitchen sink.

In general, when considering breaking the law, you need to do a
risk/benefit assessment. This is why there are often large fines
for doing trivial things you are not likely to get caught at, such as
$500.00 for littering.

It is often most efficient simply to do the right thing since it requires
the least effort in the long run. That battery may turn out to cost
you much more than a twenty minute schlep when you consider
you may be on the path to even greater social deviancy.

